w. 1988. ''Musical Events''. London: Grafton Books. {{ISBN|978-0-246-13311-3}}.\n* Rosenberg, Donald. 2000. ''The Cleveland Orchestra Story, \"Second to None\"''. Cleveland, OH: Gray and Company, Publishers. {{ISBN|978-1-886228-24-5}}.\n* Ross, Alex. 2007. ''The Rest is Noise''. New York: Farrar, Straus and Giroux. {{ISBN|978-0-374-24939-7}}.\n* Samuel, Claude. 1976. ''Conversations with Olivier Messiaen'', translated by Felix Aprahamian. London: Stainer and Bell. {{ISBN|0-85249-308-8}}.\n* Samuel, Claude (ed.). 1986. ''Eclats / Boulez'' (in French). Paris: Editions du Centre Pompidou. {{ISBN|978-2-85850-342-1}}.\n* Samuel, Claude (ed.). 2002. ''Eclats 2002'' (in French). Paris: M\u00e9moire du Livre. {{ISBN|978-2-913867-14-7}}.\n* Samuel, Claude. 2013. Notes to CD set ''Boulez: Complete Works''. France: Deutsche Grammophon. {{OCLC|985147586}}.\n* Steinegger, Catherine. 2012. ''Pierre Boulez et le th\u00e9\u00e2tre'' (in French). Wavre (Belgium): \u00c9ditions Mardaga. {{ISBN|978-2-8047-0090-4}}\n* Vermeil, Jean. 1996. ''Conversations with Boulez: Thoughts on Conducting''. Translated by Camille Nash, with a selection of programs conducted by Boulez and a discography by Paul Griffiths. Portland, OR: Amadeus Press. {{ISBN|978-1-57467-007-3}}\n* Wagner, Wolfgang. 1994. ''Acts. The Autobiography of Wolfgang Wagner''. Translated by John Brownjohn. London: Weidenfeld & Nicolson. {{ISBN|978-0-297-81349-1}}.\n* Walsh, Stephen. 2006. ''Stravinsky: the Second Exile. France and America, 1934\u20131971''. London: Jonathan Cape. {{ISBN|978-0-224-06078-3}}.\n{{div col end}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikimedia|wikt=no|c=Category:Pierre Boulez|d=Q156193|s=no|n=no}}\n\n'''Composer'''\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2-Ro3KivRaw ''Sonatine'' for flute and piano] \u2013 Sophie Cherrier / S\u00e9bastien Vichard, Cit\u00e9 de la musique, Paris, 4 December 2015.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jyZbhPVHp3k ''Livre pour cordes''] \u2013 G\u00fcrzenich-Orchester K\u00f6ln / Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Roth, K\u00f6lner Philharmonie, 5 February 2018.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Xv7S5LW3LM ''Cummings ist der Dichter''] \u2013 SWR Vokalensemble Stuttgart / Ensemble Intercontemporain / George Benjamin, Cit\u00e9 de la musique, 29 January 2013.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIlfuf2wUok ''Notations I-IV and VII''] \u2013 Frankfurt Radio Symphony Orchestra / Manfred Honeck, Alte Oper Frankfurt, 27 March 2015.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OQE5TYnD58k ''R\u00e9pons''] \u2013 Ensemble Intercontemporain / Matthias Pintscher, Philharmonie de Paris, 11 June 2015.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o0APfmT-mQs ''...explosante-fixe...''] \u2013 Emmanuelle Oph\u00e8le / Ensemble Intercontemporain / Matthias Pintscher, Philharmonie de Paris, 21 March 2015.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HCQI6Wu3QxE ''sur Incises''] \u2013 Ensemble Intercontemporain / Matthias Pintscher, Philharmonie de Paris, 18 March 2017.\n\n'''Conductor'''\n* [http://nyphil.org/watch-listen/audio/broadcasts/1516/boulez-der-wein-mahler Mahler's Symphony No.3 (audio broadcast)] \u2013 Yvonne Minton / New York Philharmonic Orchestra / Boulez, Avery Fisher Hall, New York, 1976.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ufqC1LCpHV4 Bruckner's Symphony No.8] \u2013 Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra / Boulez, Stiftskirche St. Florian, Linz, 11 October 1996.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_P8d5FxjNx0 Berg, Debussy and Stravinsky] \u2013 Christine Sch\u00e4fer / Chicago Symphony Orchestra / Boulez, Cologne Philharmonie, 25 April 2000.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yHHUxoa1DDs Schoenberg's Variations op.31] \u2013 Orchestre Philharmonique de Radio France / Boulez, Salle Pleyel, Paris, 20 February 2009.\n\n'''Documentaries'''\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_y_DMXqe1mU Pierre Boulez \u2013 Emotion and Analysis] \u2013 Boulez and the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra rehearsing Bart\u00f3k's Concerto for Orchestra in Lisbon in 2003 (in German with English subtitles).\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xFqxA-Vms24 Beyond the Score \u2013 Boulez: 'A Pierre Dream'] \u2013 a 2014 concert / documentary by the Chicago Symphony Orchestra, curated by Gerard McBurney and designed by Frank Gehry.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8nFUixrTKNk Tribute to Conductor and Composer, Pierre Boulez] \u2013 by the Cleveland Orchestra for Boulez's 90th birthday in 2015.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K04eaqNtVg4 R\u00e9pons in New York] \u2013 short documentary on the October 2017 performances of Boulez's R\u00e9pons at Park Avenue Armory in New York.\n\n'''Interviews'''\n* [https://archive.org/details/SOM_1986_02_16 Charles Amirkhanian interviews Boulez and Andrew Gerzso] as part of the Speaking of Music series, San Francisco, 16 February 1986. Boulez discusses microtonal music, spatial music and ''R\u00e9pons''.\n* [http://www.bruceduffie.com/boulez.html Two Interviews with Pierre Boulez] by Bruce Duffie, 20 February 1986 and 26 October 1987.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EfIWJ1TIgqQ Filmed interview with Boulez in 2000] with Daniel Barenboim.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ie5Ore2rjhk Filmed interview with Boulez in 2012] with Wolfgang Schaufler for his publisher, Universal Edition.\n\n'''Images'''\n* [http://www.gontiermusic.com/boulez/index.html Photographic portrait of Pierre Boulez] by Philippe Gontier.\n\n'''Other online resources'''\n* {{Britannica|75540}}\n* [http://www.universaledition.com/composers-and-works/Pierre-Boulez/composer/88/worklist#page=0 Boulez pages at Universal Edition] \u2013 publisher of most of his work, including audio extracts and a calendar of forthcoming performances.\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/3bce590b-479f-42ca-b9e0-82883e0db9a2 BBC artist page] \u2013 includes interviews with, and about, Boulez and extracts from works.\n* {{AllMusic|class=artist|id=q7088}}\n\n{{Pierre Boulez}}\n{{Twelve-tone technique}}\n{{Twelve-tone composers}}\n{{Darmstadt School}}\n{{BBCSO conductors}}\n{{Cleveland Orchestra conductors}}\n{{Intercontemporain music directors}}\n{{NYPhil music directors}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards for Pierre Boulez\n|list1=\n{{Ernst von Siemens Music Prize}}\n{{Glenn Gould Prize laureates}}\n{{GrawemeyerAwardMusicComposition}}\n{{L\u00e9onie Sonning Music Prize laureates}}\n{{Polar Music Prize}}\n{{Wolf Prize in Arts}}\n{{Gramophone Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Books|France|Music}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boulez, Pierre}}\n[[Category:Pierre Boulez| ]]\n[[Category:20th-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:BBC Symphony Orchestra]]\n[[Category:Coll\u00e8ge de France faculty]]\n[[Category:Commandeurs of the Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]]\n[[Category:Composers for cello]]\n[[Category:Composers for piano]]\n[[Category:Composers for violin]]\n[[Category:Conservatoire de Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:Deutsche Grammophon artists]]\n[[Category:French electronic musicians]]\n[[Category:Edison Classical Music Awards Oeuvreprijs winners]]\n[[Category:Ernst von Siemens Music Prize winners]]\n[[Category:French male conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:French conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:French classical composers]]\n[[Category:French male classical composers]]\n[[Category:French male writers]]\n[[Category:French music theorists]]\n[[Category:Glenn Gould Prize winners]]\n[[Category:Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award winners]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses of the Order of Saint James of the Sword]]\n[[Category:Honorary Commanders of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Honorary Members of the Royal Academy of Music]]\n[[Category:Honorary Members of the Royal Philharmonic Society]]\n[[Category:Ivor Novello Award winners]]\n[[Category:Kyoto laureates in Arts and Philosophy]]\n[[Category:Members of the Academy of the Arts, Berlin]]\n[[Category:Members of the European Academy of Sciences and Arts]]\n[[Category:Music directors of the New 